<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Nutrition</title>
    <link href='https://unpkg.com/boxicons@2.1.4/css/boxicons.min.css' rel='stylesheet'>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f7f7f7;
        }

        header {
            background-color: rgb(40 59 73);
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px;
        }
        header h1 span{
            font-size: 35px;
        }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
            max-width: 60vw;
            margin: 5px auto;
            background-color: #fff;
            box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .ntrin {
            background-color: #ddd;
        }

        .plan {
            font-size: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
        }
        p{
            font-size: 18px;
        }

        .plan:hover {
            transform: scale(1.05);
            box-shadow: 0px 0px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        }

        h2 {
            color: #496787;
        }

        /* Modal Styles */
        /* ... (modal styles similar to previous examples) ... */
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="maincontainer">
        {{>navbar}}



        <div class="ntrin">
            <header>
                <h1><span id="element"></span></h1>
            </header>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="plan" onclick="showDetails(1)">
                    <h2>Weight Loss Plan</h2>
                    <p>
                        Weight loss plans are designed to help individuals lose excess body weight. They often involve
                        creating
                        a caloric deficit through a combination of reduced calorie intake and increased physical
                        activity.
                        These
                        plans may also emphasize portion control and nutrient-dense foods....
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="plan" onclick="showDetails(2)">
                    <h2>Muscle Gain Plan</h2>
                    <p>
                        Muscle gain plans, also known as bulking plans, aim to increase muscle mass and strength. They
                        usually
                        involve a higher caloric intake, focusing on protein-rich foods and targeted strength training
                        exercises....
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="plan" onclick="showDetails(3)">
                    <h2>General Health and Wellness Plan</h2>
                    <p>
                        This type of plan focuses on maintaining overall health and wellness. It typically includes a
                        balanced
                        diet with a variety of nutrients and regular physical activity, such as a mix of cardiovascular
                        exercises, strength training, and flexibility exercises....
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="plan" onclick="showDetails(4)">
                    <h2>Athletic Performance Plan</h2>
                    <p>
                        Athletes require specialized plans tailored to their specific sport and performance goals. These
                        plans
                        focus on optimizing nutrition for energy, endurance, strength, and recovery, often including
                        specific
                        nutrient timing strategies....
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="plan" onclick="showDetails(5)">
                    <h2>High-Protein Plan</h2>
                    <p>
                        This plan emphasizes a higher intake of protein, which is essential for muscle repair and
                        growth.
                        It's
                        commonly followed by those looking to build muscle or maintain muscle mass while losing
                        weight....
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="plan" onclick="showDetails(6)">
                    <h2>Vegetarian or Vegan Plan</h2>
                    <p>
                        These plans exclude meat (vegetarian) or all animal products (vegan). Proper planning is
                        important
                        to
                        ensure adequate intake of essential nutrients like protein, iron, calcium, and vitamin B12....
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="plan" onclick="showDetails(7)">
                    <h2>Functional Fitness Plan</h2>
                    <p>
                        This plan focuses on exercises that mimic everyday movements and improve overall functional
                        strength
                        and
                        mobility. It's especially beneficial for enhancing quality of life and preventing injuries....
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="plan" onclick="showDetails(8)">
                    <h2>CrossFit Plan</h2>
                    <p>
                        CrossFit combines elements of high-intensity interval training (HIIT), weightlifting, and
                        functional
                        movements to promote overall fitness. Workouts are varied and intense....
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="plan" onclick="showDetails(8)">
                    <h2>Bodyweight Training Plan</h2>
                    <p>
                        This plan utilizes the resistance of one's own body weight to build strength, flexibility, and
                        endurance. It's often convenient for those who prefer to work out at home or lack access to gym
                        equipment....
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="plan" onclick="showDetails(8)">
                    <h2>Senior Fitness Plan</h2>
                    <p>
                        Designed for older adults, this plan focuses on maintaining mobility, balance, and overall
                        health.
                        It
                        typically includes low-impact exercises and activities that cater to age-related
                        considerations...
                    </p>
                </div>
                <!-- Add more plans as needed -->
            </div>
            <div id="detailsModal">
                <div class="modal-content">
                    <h2 id="modalTitle"></h2>
                    <p id="modalContent"></p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>



        {{>footer}}
    </div>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/typed.js@2.0.16/dist/typed.umd.js"></script>
    <script>
        var typed = new Typed('#element', {
            strings: ['Nutrition and Fitness Plans'],
            typeSpeed: 50,
        });
    </script>
</body>

</html>